600048.text: The ripped paper reads: It's been three days since I came into the tower for treasure. Found no way out... I hope the captain can help us out...

600049.text: The ripped paper reads: ... it seems eerie here. I hope to face no danger...

600056.text: The stele inscribed: God's blessings stay in Irminsul long—A Glorious Country, the Celestial Year 473, Monument of the Harvest.

600057.text: Ripped page: The plants in the woods nearby have been overgrowing since yesterday. The vines in the courtyard have crept into the room through the window.

600058.text: Even the river outside the village has turned green today. Unrest fills me. I hope everything is all right.

600059.text: The stele inscribed: No harvests. The great Protector is furious. The Celestial Year 474.

600060.text: Ripped page: People around me became abnormal. Neighbors stopped going to work. Some even smashed their furniture.

600061.text: Horrible! The great Protector, save the poor, please!

600062.text: The words on the ripped page are barely legible: Unbelievable. Even I... the feeling... terrible... My hands...

600063.text: Ah! What have I become? The great Protector, why do you shower this catastrophe on me?

600064.text: Ripped page: Ah, it hurts! I had to run out. It's terrible. How come my dear Vivian attacked me with a knife!

600067.text: Market—Esha. May the Protector shelter this land.

600068.text: May it flourish. May the Protector shelter us.

600069.text: Dear... We, household guards, have not seen the Protector for some time... She locked herself in... rumors... strange magic study...

600070.text: As a household guard, glory prevents me from doubting my Lord... My faith seems not firm enough...

600071.text: Dear... Rumors are spreading among the guards... How can a glorious household guard doubt the Protector?

600072.text: The Protector has been blessing Irminsul... My sword aims to guard this land...

600073.text: ... How... This whole tragedy... is the cause of the Protector... The magic... suffering...

600115.text: Eddine, an artificial butterfly-like monster that exists only in the Dreamworld. Its wings flutter gently, full of a mysterious aura.

600116.text: Whenever Eddine shows up, swarms of fluorescent butterflies encircled it, flapping their wings with Eddine, and flying into the Dreamworld.

600117.text: It can be affirmed that Eddine is fantastic, but it's also so real. Who gets into the dream changed into a butterfly as though, haunted by Eddine's whispers, guided by the swarms of butterflies to fly into the depths of the Dreamworld.

600118.text: Each encounter with Eddine is different. Anyone who enters the Dreamland has their mind, so what is seen in the dream is individual. The hazy glow of the butterfly makes people forget the time, even sleep in the Dreamland forever.

600119.text: Though faintly, the flap of butterflies' wings will make a breeze. So the aura of magic spread and only those who entered the Dreamworld could feel it. Some even treated the breeze as the proof that this place is also a part of reality.

600120.text: Eddine will meet the mission from its creator finally, and return to the Dreamworld with butterflies, or disappear dream's doom. Before that, however, Eddine will still guide who enters to be befuddled in the depths of the Dreamworld.

600121.text: Its origin was people's fear of the unknown. Then it materialized to become a monster that deludes and controls minds.

600122.text: Dark feelings piled up. Who dared not to face the reality turned to escape everything and even eventually feared itself, which gave birth to the Fear of Shadow.

600123.text: The darkness in the Dreamworld started to merge with the darkness in the heart. Finally, it became an aggregation of fear. From the depth of this darkness surged more negative magic, and it finally started its long tread on a perilous road.

600124.text: When its vessel couldn't hold the fear, the leaked negative feelings and the forbidden in the abyss merged, and evolved into the greatest despair and the nightmare of the Dreamworld, gnawing at minds and forcing them down into the abyss.

600125.text: Roaring in chains, Oladir seems to have lost his mind, with only destructive rage left.

600126.text: Oladir used to be the best warrior of the tribe. His sturdy build could withstand unimaginable attacks. Even the most feral beasts would fall to his prey.

600127.text: Ereshkigal appreciated his combat ability, bound his huge body with the Dreamworld Chain to control his soul, and brought him to the Dreamworld. In agony, the trapped Oladir lost his pride as a warrior, attacking everything madly in sight.

600128.text: Confined by the chain, Gramel gave off unusual magic. His figure is barely recognizable due to the corrosion from the abyss.

600129.text: Gramel was a renowned young man in the Upper Domain of Cassiel, and the most promising Sorcerers in the Magical Guards. But clearly the man here has lost his mind, and the aura of the scourge from his corroded figure is thrilling.

600130.text: Gramel's magic is similar to the forbidden in the abyss, which attracted Ereshkigal to bind his soul with the Dreamworld Chain, trapping him there forever. His resentment became the source of magic, cursing those who enter the Dreamworld.

600131.text: Even bound in chains, corroded by the abyss, it can still be told that Diaz Vival was a brave chevalier, holding a shield and sword in his hands.

600132.text: The chevalier of the abyss has lost his glory. His howl that echoes throughout the Dreamworld is the only way he could vent his indignation.

600133.text: Once in the Frost Chivalric Order in Snegurochka, Diaz Vival swore an oath to the most respected Protector by his Shield. But he was bound with the Dreamworld Chain to use his claymore and grand shield to kill strayers in the Dreamworld.

600134.text: Soluk, the warrior loyal to Ereshkigal, masters not only magic but also huge hammer-shaped weapons. Anyone who tries to challenge him will suffer.

600135.text: Soluk can imbue magic into his maul, which will unleash tremendous energy after charging for a short time. You will be taught a lesson if you only treat him as a spell caster.

600136.text: As a weapon master, Soluk also performs sophisticated conjuring. He can easily choose between physical ATK and magic ATK to deal with different enemies swiftly.

600137.text: A charged maul strike consumes a large amount of magic, but Soluk's stamina seems inexhaustible. He can enhance his maul with conjuring in a short time, and use them to keep pounding foes.

600138.text: By order of Ereshkigal, Soluk assassinated any who disobey. It is said he has mastered all tools of an assassin. Killing those who rebelled against the Protector is a cinch to him.

600139.text: Soluk's swordsmanship can enhance his mind to become concentrated, and devoted himself to the combat ahead, defeating all of Ereshkigal's foes.

600140.text: Soluk's ego makes him look down upon the weak. He only speaks with them by the dagger in his hand. He can finish off the puny deftly with precision, like a streak of lightning.

600141.text: Unlike other assassins, Soluk has strong stamina and can carry out any assassination quests for a long time. He can wait patiently through late nights until the target shows a flaw.

600142.text: Soluk was a pure martial artist. To defeat sorcerers defying Ereshkigal, he decided to learn magic. Luckily, he got help from Ereshkigal. His eagerness made him master magic soon. Sorcerers who boasted before can no longer match him.

600143.text: Soluk's fire magic is as unbelievably destructive as his sword, incinerating everything in sight with no mercy.

600144.text: The spells taught by Ereshkigal also consume much magic. But for Soluk it's easy. He can restrain enemies' magic and harass his foes, and observe their actions. Obviously, this proud martial artist quite enjoys the fun of combat.

600145.text: Soluk's dark magic can erode enemies' minds, dealing damage in a short time, and crushing all who defy Ereshkigal. His loyalty makes him a killing machine, which can adapt to different situations and defeat any enemies relentlessly.

600166.text: It's my first time hearing about the Mid-Autumn Festival.

600170.text: The Isles to the east of Sunrise Island have long been neglected.

600171.text: Cut off from the outside world, trade and commerce is non-existent here.

600172.text: The lush and evergreen environs of the Isle make it suitable for living.

600173.text: The abundance and variety of seafood here has given rise to many specialty cuisines.

600174.text: The most popular cuisines are Grilled Sea Urchin, Grilled Eel, Calamari Teppanyaki, and Salt-roasted Shrimp.

600175.text: With the influx of outsiders, new cuisines like Takoyaki have also taken root.

600176.text: Yothaya loves seahorses, and wants to take them back to her home.

600177.text: Tama, who has long been stuck indoors, finally has a chance to enjoy sunbathing.

600178.text: Akasha seems to have taken some sort of souvenir from the Isles.

600179.text: Sybriette is reveling in the joys of a new acquaintance.

600180.text: Suigetsu hopes that she'll be able to vacation in the Isles every summer.

600181.text: For the villagers, the greatest blessing is a calm and placid life.
